<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="586" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5082/106.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Special Commissioner <persName type="from">Buchanan</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Willemstadt</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-02-11"><hi rend="italic">February 11,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Buchanan reports the settlement of entire Bermudez case, which has
                            been accepted by Bartlett and ratified by cabinet. Adds that protocol
                            has been equally ratified and that he is leaving for United States.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>